column1: #Text=The video , which was uploaded to the video sharing website on July 15 , became the most viewed of all time last month after overtaking the music video for " Baby " , a song by Canadian singer Justin Bieber , which was placed on YouTube two years ago .
#Text=[ T]his song is actually poking fun at those kinds of people who are trying so hard to be something that they 're not — Park Jae-Sang
#Text=With more than 6.1 million likes , Guinness World Records has recognised " Gangnam Style " as being the most liked YouTube video ever ; it also has over 449,000 dislikes .
#Text=' officialpsy ' , the YouTube channel upon which the video was uploaded , now has in excess of 2.1 million subscribers and has achieved over 1.4 billion video views overall .
#Text=According to Google , the company which owns YouTube , the video has attracted between seven and ten million daily views on average since being uploaded to the site .
#Text=Park Jae-Sang , the actual name of Psy , explained the meaning of the song in an August 2012 interview with CNN .

#Text= Gangnam Style " has inspired countless parody versions , prompting UK newspaper The Daily Telegraph to suggest it was " the most parodied video ever " .

column1: #Text=Among the parody versions are one performed by inmates of the Philippines ' Cebu Provincial Detention and Rehabilitation Center , one with students from Eton College in the United Kingdom , one from Chinese artist Ai Weiwei and one created in the approach to the 2012 United States presidential election called " Mitt Romney Style " .

#Text=Numerous prominent figures have attempted to imitate the " Gangnam Style " dance — which involves crossing one 's wrists over each other and motioning as if " you 're riding an invisible horse in your lower body , " Park Jae-Sang explained — including United Nations Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon , US President Barack Obama and Google chairman Eric Schmidt .
